&quot;Max Karl Wilhelm von Gallwitz (2 May 1852 – 18 April 1937) was a German general from Breslau (Wrocław), Silesia, who served with distinction during World War I on both the Eastern and Western Fronts.&quot;
<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Max_von_Gallwitz" rel="nofollow">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Max_von_Gallwitz</a>

Towards the end of 1915 he succeeded Mackensen as commander of the Eleventh Army and led the campaign against Serbia (under the command of Mackensen, who was promotet to field marshall).
